domain.product

Class Product

  • java.lang.Object
    • domain.product.Product
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IDeepCopy, IProduct, IShoppingCartElement
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    JointProduct, SimpleProduct

    public abstract class Product
extends Object
implements IProduct, IShoppingCartElement
    This class is used to encapsulate the basic properties of a product. In this case a product consists of two attributes: its name and its price. This class is used as a common abstract superclass to concrete implementations given further down in the hierarchy.

    Attributes of the class:

    • price of the product (as a point number)
    • name of the product
    • category of the product

        public abstract Product deepCopy()

        Creates and returns a copy of this object. The precise meaning of "copy" may depend on the class of the object. The general intent is that, for any object x, the expression:
